1581: Microbial sample-Lactobacillus paragasseri UBLG-36
Identifiers: BioSample: SAMN15733757; Sample name: VITLG-UBLG-36; SRA: SRS7168354
Organism: Lactobacillus paragasseri
Attributes:
    /strain="UBLG-36"
    /isolation source="gut"
    /host="Homo sapiens"
    /collection date="2015-07-02"
    /geographic location="India: Hyderabad"
    /sample type="Bacteria colony"
    /biomaterial provider="Unique Biotech Ltd"
    /collected by="Vellore Institute of Technology"
Description:
Lactobacilli are common inhabitants of the human gut flora and confer many health benefits. Mammals rely on the ability of the gut microbiota to degrade oxalate as mammals lack the necessary enzymes for this process. Here, we report the draft genome sequence of Lactobacillus paragasseri UBLG-36 in order to study the genetics behind the ability of the bacteria to degrade oxalate.
Accession: SAMN15733757	ID: 15733757
